Data
----

We start by loading the Wind speed data into R and convert the column
`Newdate` into R's `Date` format.

    site1 <- read.csv("../../data/week2/windspeed.csv")
    site1$Newdate <- as.Date(site1$Newdate)

We can now plot the data (we'll use the formula notation `y~x` to
specify what which variables to use for the x and y axes).

    plot(WindSpeed~Newdate, data=site1, ylab="Wind Speed", xlab="Year", 
         pch=19, cex=0.2, col=2)
    title("Wind Speed")

<img src="data:image/png;base64," width=".45\textwidth" />

To reduce the clutter we can calculate the average wind speed for every
day. This can be done very efficiently using the function `aggregate`.

    # Calculate dailCon vert the date to a date#Wind speed
    agg_mean <- aggregate(site1$WindSpeed, by=list(Date=site1$Newdate), mean)
    head(agg_mean)

    ##         Date         x
    ## 1 2011-01-01 10.686957
    ## 2 2011-01-02  7.667917
    ## 3 2011-01-03        NA
    ## 4 2011-01-04        NA
    ## 5 2011-01-05  8.376667
    ## 6 2011-01-06  8.535417

We can now plot the daily average wind speed as a line

    plot(x~Date, data=agg_mean, ylab="Wind Speed", xlab="Year", 
         type="l", col=2)
    title("Wind Speed")
